description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role: Experienced Care Support Worker -Acute Hospital Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Chesterfield Royal Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Flexible Working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£9.21 per hour – Days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£12.98 per hour – Saturday &amp; Nights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£16.85 per hour – Sunday &amp; Bank Holiday&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nestled in the heart of Derbyshire, Chesterfield is a market town famed for its Crooked Spire. North Derbyshire&#39;s only acute district general hospital, with 24 hour Emergency Department services, we&#39;re responsible for providing care and treatment to more than 400,000 people who live in our communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Chesterfield Royal Hospital NHS Foundation Trust we are PROUD TO CARE, not only for our patients and visitors but also for our staff. This is highlighted through our Friends and Family Test in which 98% of patients would recommend the Chesterfield Trust along with 70% of employees recommending working at Chesterfield Hospital in the recent trust staff survey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have flexible working opportunities available for experienced Care Support Workers. Offering first choice of shifts at a Trust Rated ‘Good’ overall and ‘Excellent’ for End of Life Care by the CQC?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;To apply for this post, you must have&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Have a minimum of 3 months&#39; care support worker experience in either an acute hospital or hospice which has been gained in the last two years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You must also hold one of the following qualifications dated in the last five years obtaining level 2 or above:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- NVQ/QCF/Apprenticeship Diploma in Health and Social Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Care Certificate from an NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;OR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a nursing student and have completed at least 12 weeks of placements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants must be competent in taking the following practical observations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manual Blood Pressure, Respirations and a Pulse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates &lt;/strong&gt;- work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of shifts at your Trust&lt;/strong&gt; – Access to shifts before they are available to agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working to suit your lifestyle &lt;/strong&gt;– Take control of when you want to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Book and manage your shifts on the go&lt;/strong&gt; – Access shifts anywhere, anytime online or through your smartphone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that you will be contacted via email throughout the recruitment process, so please check your emails regularly. (including junk/spam folders)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We regret we cannot contact everyone who is not selected for an interview, therefore if you do not hear from us within 21 days after submitting your application, please assume you have not been successful on this occasion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We may close the vacancy before the specified date if we have a high number of applicants. &lt;/p&gt;
